<article>
    <h1>Keep your ve&#xAD;hi&#xAD;cle COVID-19 free</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200903/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-03"><time>2020-09-03</time></a>
        - <span>CLASSIFIED&#xAD;S</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>While we take steps to en­hance our per­sonal hy­giene to pre­vent COVID-19 in­fec­tion, we have to also take note of dis­in­fect­ing our ve­hi­cles.</p>
    <p>When an in­fected per­son coughs or ex­hales, small droplets from the nose or mouth land on sur­faces in the car. Other pas­sen­gers can get in­fected when they touch sur­faces with the virus, and then touch their eyes, nose, or mouth.</p>
    <p>Take note of these tips to stay safe from the virus while in your ve­hi­cles.</p>
    <p>USE SOAP AND WA­TER</p>
    <p>Soap de­stroys viruses by break­ing them down, like how it does to oils.</p>
    <p>Wear dis­pos­able gloves while clean­ing your car in­te­rior to pro­tect your­self against COVID-19.</p>
    <p>NO HARSH CHEM­I­CALS</p>
    <p>When clean­ing your car, avoid us­ing dis­in­fec­tants and clean­ing prod­ucts that con­tain any of the fol­low­ing harsh chem­i­cals such as bleach, hy­dro­gen per­ox­ide, am­mo­nia, ace­tone, al­co­hols, kerosene and other sol­vents.</p>
    <p>With the ex­cep­tion of bleach and hy­dro­gen per­ox­ide, these chem­i­cals don’t re­ally harm viruses. Again, us­ing soap for dis­in­fect­ing your car should suf­fice.</p>
    <p>WASH SUR­FACES VIG­OR­OUSLY</p>
    <p>Scrub sur­faces in­side and out­side the ve­hi­cle with a mi­crofi­bre cloth. Vig­or­ous wash­ing al­lows soap and wa­ter to sur­round the coro­n­avirus’s pro­tec­tive en­ve­lope. Fric­tion caused by scrub­bing breaks the virus down.</p>
    <p>But please do not scrub so hard that you end up with faded, torn, or tat­tered car seats.</p>
    <p>CLEAN FRE­QUENTLY TOUCHED SUR­FACE</p>
    <p>Thor­oughly clean sur­faces that are fre­quently touched, in­clud­ing door han­dle, dash­board, steer­ing wheel, gear shifter, key fob, but­tons and switches, seat­belts, touch­screens, arm­rests, seat ad­justers and rearview mir­ror.</p>
    <p>PRO­FES­SIONAL SER­VICES</p>
    <p>If you are not con­fi­dent about clean­ing your car by your­self, let a pro­fes­sional han­dle your car san­i­ta­tion.</p>
    <p>You can drive your car to the near­est car wash, or book a car san­i­ta­tion ser­vice.</p>
    <p>It is good to leave no stone un­turned dur­ing these times as we can­not af­ford to let our guard down. So keep calm and clean your car, lorry, mo­tor­cy­cle, pickup or minibus to pro­tect your­self and your loved ones against COVID-19!</p>

